{
  "text": "Therefore, in order to overcome these issues, engineered scaffolds have been proposed as strategies for delivery SCs and improve regeneration after SCI [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Axonal regeneration in turn favor functional recovery, such as locomotor and sensorial improvements. In recent years, a variety of biomaterials have been employed in tissue engineering in order to support the regeneration of neural structures damaged after SCI.",
